description: For sale: $94,900. House sustained fire/smoke damage throughout, see prior listing for pre-fire pics. Being sold as is. Cute home on hilltop in highly sought-after neighborhood. Original woodwork with 5" casing and base molding throughout most of the home. Nine foot ceilings! All white faux wood blinds included. Huge, flat city lot with plenty of sun in rear. Perfect for a garden and some chickens! Easy access to public transportation and walking distance to Smith Ave shops and the scenic Highbridge. A great number of parks nearby including the Battle Creek and Cherokee Regional Parks, both on the mighty Mississippi. Highbridge Dog Park is just 2 miles! Numerous lakes surround. A half dozen golf courses including Highland National Public Golf, Mendakota and Somerset Country Clubs. Just miles from downtown St. Paul. Less than 10 miles to both MSP Int'l Airport and St. Paul Airport.

  Take a thorough look at our website at www.lowertownlofts.org and click on 'Live Here' to find out more about buying a share in, and becoming a working member/owner of an active housing cooperative, and whether it is the right home ownership option for you as a creative.

- Email lowertownloftscoop@gmail.com with any questions and for more information 

Financing info: https://mn.hb101.org/a/6/

-This is not a rental.

-This is a Live/Workspace to own within a coop for creatives with a lower cost of living. No, you do not have to be an artist, but you do have to Homestead.

description: Recently sold: $225,000. Loaded with old world charm, this Ramsey Hill top floor unit is filled with original detail and updated features. As you enter you will notice the hardwood floors throughout, the beautiful original woodwork and 11 foot ceilings. The living room is stunning with the original carved fireplace mantel, bay window with full width window seat, working pocket door and unique piano nook with its own closet. The large formal dining room features a beautiful built in with secret passage. This room could also make a great family room. Rare, large eat in kitchen featuring, built in cabinets that provide abundant storage, a gas range, granite countertop, great natural light from south and went facing windows and convenient office/desk area. The kitchen leads out to a private balcony space for seasonal enjoyment. The home also has 2 good sized bedrooms and an updated bath. Best of all, you will have a short walk to all of the great restaurants, coffee shops and parks that Ramsey Hill offers.

description: Recently sold: $160,000.

Recently sold: $355,000. Premier Summit Avenue location. Classic Saint Paul Summit Avenue 2 bed plus den condo located in historically significant 1898 Clarence Johnston designed luxury apartment building. Top floor, elegantly proportioned rooms with 10ft ceilings and original details including decorative fireplace, hardwood floors, built-in buffet, columns, moldings and doors. Custom architect designed kitchen and bathroom renovation with high end finishes and appliances. French doors leading from living room to private tree top deck. In-unit laundry. This is a special building and a glorious home. The condo, located within the vibrant Historic Ramsey Hill neighborhood is one block from the University Club and within several blocks of 3 city parks, as well within walking distance to the great restaurants and shops of Selby and Grand Avenues. Downtown St. Paul, the St. Paul Cathedral and the Minnesota State Capitol also are all within walking distance. Urban living at its finest.

Don't miss the wonderful opportunity to call this home. 2019-08-27

description:
Recently sold: $377,000. Fully Furnished home in GREAT location -- Summit/University/Cathedral Hill. 1000 + sq/ft. Relocating to St Paul? Move into our cheerful, light filled, south facing home that includes 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, a lofted living room, a wood burning stove, a separate dining area and a spacious kitchen. The home was recently updated with VOC free Benjamin Moore paint and new wood floors. We encourage sustainable living and will provide a compost system and space to garden, hang your wash outside and tool storage. Tenants pay electric and gas utilities. You can't beat the location. Within 3 blocks you can stroll to the Mississippi Market Natural Food Coop (www.msmarket.coop), 3 coffee shops, 5 restaurants, bakeries, home stores, gift stores and 2 pocket parks. There is another urban living district 4 blocks south, on Summit and Grand Avenues. Here you will find numerous shops, restaurants, a hardware store and more. You can reach the Green Line train to Minneapolis in a mile and the Capitol building is only 2 miles away. Some favorite eateries within blocks include: French Hen Cafe (www.frenchhencafe.com), Louisiana Cafe (www.newlouisianacafe.com), Great Harvest Bread Company (www.stpaulbread.com), Nina's Coffee Cafe (www.ninascoffeecafe.com) and WA Frost (www.wafrost.com) and Sweeny's Salon (www.sweenyssalon.com)

Universities and Elementary Schools nearby include:

Mitchel Hamline School of Law, .8 miles
Saint Paul College, 1 mile
Concordia University, 1.7 miles
Macalaster College, 2.6 miles
Barack and Michelle Obama Elementary, .3 miles
JJ Hill Montessori, .9 mile

Additional Amenities included:

* Wi-Fi
* Water and Sewer utilities
* Waste and Recycling pick up
* Air conditioning and forced air heat
* Free laundry in building
* Snow shoveling and lawn care
* Big yard and attractive fence
* Easy to clean hardwood and tile floors throughout
* All furnishings. Everything you view in the pictures and more including desk organizers and games
* Household goods from linens to soap
* King bed in master bedroom
* 2 twin beds in second bedroom
* Pets o.k. based on meeting with landlord and or references. Pet Deposit required
* New gas cooking stove
* Microwave
* Well equipped kitchen -- dishes, pots and pans, waffle maker, blender and more
* Starter pantry with organic staples from spices, oil and vinegar to Annie's Mac and Cheese
* Optional monthly social gathering with downstairs tenant to foster community
* Responsive landlord -- Contact Sonya Newenhouse for application. $2000 deposit.

Owner pays for Wifi, Waste and Recycling, Snow and Lawn Care.

description: Recently sold: $275,000. Available NOW! Absolutely gorgeous FIRST FLOOR two-bedroom, one full bath condo in fantastic St. Paul location! You will fall in love and look forward to coming home to the historic birthplace of F. Scott Fitzgerald! This home has an abundance of character, is meticulously maintained, and boasts a welcoming front porch, gorgeous hardwood floors, natural woodwork, charming exposed brick walls, spacious bedrooms, and many updates. The architecture in this building is spectacular, and every detail has been carefully thought out. You will notice this the moment you enter the common entryway with the beautiful, open staircase with carved hand railing and impressive hanging light fixture. Upon entering, the living room features the original exposed brick, a built-in bookcase, bay window, and a cute reading nook for the book lover. The kitchen has been updated and has open cupboards, granite countertops, and updated appliances. There is also a charming hidden pantry with a built-in buffet cabinet! The master bedroom is spacious with a bayed wall, two closets, hardwood floors, and ceiling fan. The second bedroom could also be used as an office and has an abundance of beautiful white built-in bookshelves. There is plenty of storage in this home outside of the unit itself. Directly off the kitchen is a nice sized storage unit that is easily accessible. In the basement of the building is a second storage unit that will accommodate bikes, seasonal items and so much more. There is also a sauna in the building's basement for some well-deserved rest and relaxation. Welcome home to this historic, hard to find condo in lovely St. Paul! Sorry, no pets allowed. Water, sewer, trash, heat, snow removal and lawn care all INCLUDED with rent!
